The paper discusses the application of deep learning to symbolic domains, specifically in the context of graph neural networks (GNNs) for multitask learning. The paper also focuses on the problem of estimating network centrality measures, which falls under the category of graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, since the paper deals with graph representations and relational learning, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories.
